04204nam a22005655i 9780520943711DE-B159720200424112023.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||200424t20092009cau    fo  d z      eng d  a97805209437117 a10.1525/97805209437112doi  a(DE-B1597)518774  a(OCoLC)664682175  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  acaucUS-CA 4aQE721.2.E85bF67 2009eb 7aSCI0310002bisacsh04a551.722200aFor the Rock Record :bGeologists on Intelligent Design /cJill S. Schneiderman, Warren D. Allmon. 1aBerkeley, CA : bUniversity of California Press, c[2009] 4cÂ©2009  a1 online resource (272 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tIntroduction -- t1. Charles Darwin Was a Geologist: Inorganic Complexity and the Rock Record -- t2. Creationist Perspectives on Geology -- t3. Missing Links Found: Transitional Forms in the Fossil Mammal Record -- t4. Pigeonholing the "Dino-birds" -- t5. Pangloss, Paley, and the Privileged Planet: Parrying the Wedge Strategy in Earth Science Education -- t6. It's Not about the Evidence: The Role of Metaphysics in the Debate -- t7. The Misguided Attack on Methodological Naturalism -- t8. On the Origin of Species and the Limits of Science -- t9. Teaching Evolution during the Week and Bible Study on Sunday -- t10. The "God Spectrum" and the Uneven Search for a Consistent View of the Natural World -- tSelected Resources Relevant to Intelligent Design -- tAbout the Contributors -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aAccording to the idea of intelligent design, nature's complexity is the result of deliberate planning by a supernatural creative force. To date, most scientific arguments against this form of creationism have been made by evolutionary biologists. In this volume, a team of earth scientists reveals that the flaws of intelligent design are not limited to the biological sciences. Indeed, the geological sciences offer some of the best refutations of intelligent design arguements. For the Rock Record is dedicated to the proposition that the idea of intelligent design should be of serious concern to everyone. Editors Jill S. Schneiderman and Warren D. Allmon have gathered leading figures from the geological community with a wide range of viewpoints that go to the heart of the debate over what is and is not science. The purveyors of intelligent design theories and its kindred philosophies threaten the scientific literacy that our society needs by confusing faith and the practice of science. This collection offers a much-needed response.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aCreation. 0aEvolutionary paleobiology. 0aHistorical geology. 0aIntelligent design (Teleology) 7aSCIENCE / Earth Sciences / Geology.2bisacsh1 aAllmon, Warren D., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchneiderman, Jill S., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520943711423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520943711.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles